==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|[[ipsō]] [[factō]]||by the same fact}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈɪpsəʊ ˌfæktəʊ/|lang=en}}

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-|head=ipso facto}}

# By that very fact itself; [[actually]]. Compare: [[eo ipso]].
#* '''1999''' April, [[w:Bryan Caplan|Bryan Caplan]], "[http://www.jstor.org/stable/1061278 The Austrian Search for Realistic Foundations]", in ''Southern Economic Journal'', volume 65, number 4, page 833:
#*: For [[w:Ludwig von Mises|[Ludwig von] Mises]] or [[w:Murray Rothbard|[Murray] Rothbard]], it is simply confused to posit latent preferences; if two individuals fail to make an exchange, then this '''ipso facto''' demonstrates that at that moment at least one of them would not have benefited from the exchange.

